{# #### `project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_url` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_url",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "4-26. Booking - Check Availability - Link (URL) [B] [IMPORTANT]", "description": """This setting defines the URL where the agent will send availability check requests.

The URL must be a valid endpoint that can handle availability check requests.

If `project_attributes_setting_booking_check_availability_type` is set to `default`, you may still
provide a Google Maps URL to your business card in case your hotel name is not unique or Google may
match it incorrectly.

When this URL is provided, the agent will use it to directly identify your business on Google Maps,
ensuring a precise and reliable availability check.

This is especially important when:

- Your business name is shared by multiple hotels or locations
- The name on Google Maps differs slightly from how guests commonly write it
- Google might incorrectly match your business based on name alone

If your business name is perfectly accurate and unique on Google, you may leave this field empty and
the agent will automatically find your business using the name.

Example URL: `https://maps.app.goo.gl/e14ZDSGkr3ps534x7`

To obtain such URL for your business:

1. Open your business in Google Maps so you see `CHECK AVAILABILITY` button.
2. Click `Share` button.
3. Click `COPY LINK` and paste it in this attribute.""", "group": "4. Agent Behavior", "is_hidden": False }
)}}

