    value={ "title": "5-11. ASR - Minimum Bill Amount For Large Group Reservation Per Day [A]", "description": """This setting defines the minimum bill amount required for large group reservations per day and is
used in ASR (Average Sales Revenue) calculations.

It ensures that revenue calculations meet a baseline amount, even if the per-person bill total is
lower.

How it works:

- The value should be a number, representing the minimum amount (in currency) required for a large
  group reservation
- If a reservation's total falls below this value, the minimum bill amount will be used instead for
  ASR calculations
- Helps ensure more accurate revenue tracking for large group bookings

Example usage:

- Average bill per person per day: $200
- Number of people: 10
- Total calculated amount: 10 × $200 = $2000
- Minimum large group bill set: $2500
- Since $2000 is below the minimum, the ASR calculation will use $2500 instead""", "group": "5. Reports", "value_type": "number", "is_hidden": False }
)}}

